00117Fr 2               ;   Inline-ported from msbasic-master/{var,array,string,memory}.s and
00117Fr 2               ;   misc2.s (GivAyf/SngFlt).  All MSBASIC externals are resolved here:
00117Fr 2               ;
00117Fr 2               ;     SynErr / MemErr / IqErr / Gme / SubErr        - error trampolines
00117Fr 2               ;     ChkCom / ChkCls / ChkNum / ChkStr             - parser predicates
00117Fr 2               ;     MakInt / FrmNum / FrmEvl                      - minimal stubs (only
00117Fr 2               ;                                                     handle literal unsigned
00117Fr 2               ;                                                     decimals via Fin; full
00117Fr 2               ;                                                     evaluator wired in a
00117Fr 2               ;                                                     later phase)
00117Fr 2               ;     IsLetC                                        - ASCII letter test
00117Fr 2               ;     PtrGet / Array / GetAry                       - variable lookup
00117Fr 2               ;     StrIni / StrSpa / GetSpa / PutNew / MovStr    - string allocation
00117Fr 2               ;     Garbag (and helpers)                          - string GC
00117Fr 2               ;     Bltu / Reason                                 - block-up-move helpers
00117Fr 2               ;     AyInt / GivAyf / SngFlt                       - FP <-> 16-bit int
00117Fr 2               ;     BasCmdClr                                     - implements CLR / NEW core
00117Fr 2               ; =============================================================================
00117Fr 2               
00117Fr 2               ; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
00117Fr 2               ; SynErr / MemErr / IqErr / SubErr / Gme -- error trampolines.
00117Fr 2               ; The msbasic convention is "ldx #code; jmp ERROR".  Our BasError takes the
00117Fr 2               ; code in A, so translate; BasErrorVec (defined earlier) does that translation.
00117Fr 2               ; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
00117Fr 2               SynErr:
00117Fr 2  A2 00                ldx     #ERR_SYNTAX
001181r 2  4C rr rr             jmp     BasErrorVec
001184r 2               
001184r 2               MemErr:
001184r 2  A2 02                ldx     #ERR_MEMFULL
001186r 2  4C rr rr             jmp     BasErrorVec
001189r 2               
001189r 2               SubErr:
001189r 2  A2 04                ldx     #ERR_BADSUBS
00118Br 2  4C rr rr             jmp     BasErrorVec
00118Er 2               
00118Er 2               Gse:
00118Er 2  4C rr rr             jmp     SubErr
001191r 2               
001191r 2               Gme:
001191r 2  4C rr rr             jmp     MemErr
001194r 2               
