002AD4r 2               ; Wrappers so the dispatch table can call existing routines that expect
002AD4r 2               ; TXTPTR positioned already.
002AD4r 2               BasCmdPrintW:
002AD4r 2                       ; We were entered via the dispatch trampoline, so TXTPTR is already
002AD4r 2                       ; past the PRINT token (ChrGet was tail-called).  But BasCmdPrint
002AD4r 2                       ; expects to consume the token itself with its first ChrGet; rewind.
002AD4r 2                       ; Easier: BasCmdPrint reads via ChrGet; here ChrGet was called before
002AD4r 2                       ; routine entry, so TXTPTR currently points at first arg.  Just call
002AD4r 2                       ; an internal entry that skips the leading ChrGet.
002AD4r 2  4C rr rr             jmp     BasPrLoop
